Current thinking in lipid lowering. In addition to elevated low-density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol, which has been conclusively proven to play a critical role in atherogenesis and coronary artery disease (CAD), other lipoprotein abnormalities are associated with CAD, such as reduced high-density lipoprotein (HDL) cholesterol increased triglyceride-rich lipoproteins (very low density and intermediate-density lipoproteins)